WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
You can create a draft playlist by using the 'Clip' button in the video player or by using the timeline and rowwise event data in the bottom container.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Add any notes or tags to the clip, and change the 'lead time' to search the start the clip.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:27.000
Hit the 'add to draft playlist' button to move the clip into the playlist container. You can then export the clip as an mp4 or continue adding clips to the draft playlist.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:35.000
You can also use the rowwise table data to search and filter events using the table headers. 

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:53.000
This example, uses the connections data to make a playlist of Maddy Gordon's first phase receives.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:05.000
The draft playlist can then be used to search each event in the video by selecting the table row.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:21.000
You can also save the draft playlist to view later or to export individual clips in the playlist.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Select the saved playlist and hit 'Move to draft' to view or export a single clip in the playlist.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:34.000
Or, select the saved playlist and hit 'Export clip' to export a zip folder containing all clips in the playlist.